WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:04:00.597 --> 00:04:02.557
Forgive me. Consul Han...

3
00:04:02.598 --> 00:04:05.685
but I believe
we can ill afford...

4
00:04:05.726 --> 00:04:08.729
to lose men
of your high character.

5
00:04:08.771 --> 00:04:11.148
And speaking as a friend...

6
00:04:11.190 --> 00:04:14.693
who's fought side by side
with you for 15 years...

7
00:04:14.735 --> 00:04:17.112
I will sorely miss
the unshakable support...

8
00:04:17.153 --> 00:04:19.072
you've given
the Royal Hong Kong Police.

9
00:04:19.072 --> 00:04:22.408
So. on behalf of all Brits...

10
00:04:22.408 --> 00:04:24.702
who have ever carried the shield
in Hong Kong...

11
00:04:24.744 --> 00:04:26.037
we shall miss you.

12
00:04:26.078 --> 00:04:27.830
We wish you nothing
but happiness...

13
00:04:27.872 --> 00:04:30.374
as you take up your new post
in the United States.

14
00:04:30.416 --> 00:04:33.418
Ladies and gentlemen.
Consul Han.

15
00:04:34.753 --> 00:04:36.254
Thank you. Thomas.

16
00:04:39.924 --> 00:04:44.053
You know Thomas is not going
to make this evening easy.

17
00:04:44.095 --> 00:04:45.263
Excuse me.

18
00:04:52.102 --> 00:04:53.270
Commander Griffin...

19
00:04:53.312 --> 00:04:55.981
I am pleased to be able
to leave you and Hong Kong...

20
00:04:56.022 --> 00:04:58.275
with a special gift tonight.

21
00:04:58.275 --> 00:05:00.860
Earlier this evening.
Detective inspector Lee...

22
00:05:00.902 --> 00:05:03.654
and his special task force
have once and for all...

23
00:05:03.696 --> 00:05:05.448
crushed the Juntao
criminal organization...

24
00:05:05.489 --> 00:05:07.408
and reclaimed artifacts...

25
00:05:07.450 --> 00:05:10.035
from 5.000 years
of China's heritage.

26
00:05:12.663 --> 00:05:14.122
Thank you.

27
00:05:15.791 --> 00:05:18.209
This is the kind of legacy
I dreamt about.

28
00:05:18.918 --> 00:05:20.420
Hong Kong forever.

29
00:05:20.462 --> 00:05:22.964
To Hong Kong forever.

30
00:05:30.262 --> 00:05:31.430
Soo Yung.

31
00:06:10.466 --> 00:06:11.925
Stupid fool!

32
00:06:11.967 --> 00:06:15.470
Get the hell out of my way!
Man. are you crazy?

33
00:06:15.512 --> 00:06:16.638
Shoot!

34
00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:17.931
You moron!

35
00:06:24.061 --> 00:06:26.605
Clive. what's up. man?

36
00:06:26.647 --> 00:06:28.774
You're late.

37
00:06:28.816 --> 00:06:30.693
-I'm late?
-Yeah. you're late.

38
00:06:30.693 --> 00:06:34.071
I've been waiting
in the back for over an hour.

39
00:06:34.112 --> 00:06:36.656
-I was in the diner.
-I told you in the back.

40
00:06:36.698 --> 00:06:38.867
Think I would do this shit
out front?

41
00:06:38.908 --> 00:06:41.536
-I'm gonna get busted.
-You weren't in the diner.

42
00:06:41.578 --> 00:06:43.955
I said in the back--
It don't even matter.

43
00:06:43.996 --> 00:06:47.416
Let's do this.
What's that. a gun?

44
00:06:47.458 --> 00:06:49.376
How many people
you killed this year?

45
00:06:49.376 --> 00:06:51.962
Stop it. man.
Let's do it. Come on.

46
00:06:52.004 --> 00:06:53.172
Don't be late again.

47
00:06:53.213 --> 00:06:55.257
I ain't gonna be late.
What we got?

48
00:06:57.050 --> 00:06:58.718
That's tight.

49
00:06:58.760 --> 00:07:01.471
That's beautiful. That's nice.
What's that?

50
00:07:01.512 --> 00:07:04.599
-That's C-4.
-That's C-4?

51
00:07:04.640 --> 00:07:06.934
-Oh. shit.
-What's the problem?

52
00:07:06.976 --> 00:07:09.603
No problem. I been looking
everywhere for this shit.

53
00:07:09.645 --> 00:07:13.232
How the hell you find some C-4?

54
00:07:13.273 --> 00:07:15.525
The Iraqis
can't even get this shit.

55
00:07:15.567 --> 00:07:17.194
Where'd you get this from?

56
00:07:17.235 --> 00:07:18.528
It's a hot ticket.

57
00:07:18.570 --> 00:07:20.655
You don't know how happy
you made me.

58
00:07:20.697 --> 00:07:23.199
You got what I want.
Let me get that money.

59
00:07:23.241 --> 00:07:24.492
Step away from the car.

60
00:07:24.534 --> 00:07:26.702
Hey. officers.

61
00:07:26.744 --> 00:07:29.580
Put your hands above your heads.
Just do it now.

62
00:07:29.622 --> 00:07:32.666
Ain't no problem here.
Why y'all messing with us for?

63
00:07:32.708 --> 00:07:34.584
All right. take it easy.

64
00:07:34.626 --> 00:07:36.670
-You don't wanna do that.
-Yes. I do.

65
00:07:36.711 --> 00:07:39.422
-No. he don't. He's playing.
-No. I ain't playing.

66
00:07:39.464 --> 00:07:41.883
-Yes. he is. officer.
-I'm not playing!

67
00:07:41.925 --> 00:07:43.051
Drop the gun!

68
00:07:43.092 --> 00:07:44.886
He's just my cousin.
We're just talking.

69
00:07:44.927 --> 00:07:46.387
Get in your car and leave.

70
00:07:46.429 --> 00:07:47.763
We can't do that.

71
00:07:47.805 --> 00:07:50.224
I'll blow his head
all over the parking lot!

72
00:07:50.266 --> 00:07:51.600
Go away and buy some doughnuts!

73
00:07:51.642 --> 00:07:53.060
See? You made him mad.

74
00:07:53.101 --> 00:07:55.228
Let me talk to him.
All right?

75
00:07:56.271 --> 00:07:57.522
Don't move!

76
00:07:57.564 --> 00:08:00.191
All right.
Everything's cool now.

77
00:08:00.233 --> 00:08:03.444
He down. The gun's down.
Get back in the car and leave.

78
00:08:03.486 --> 00:08:04.612
Hands on your head!

79
00:08:04.654 --> 00:08:06.405
Everything's cool. officer.

80
00:08:06.447 --> 00:08:07.615
Do it now!

81
00:08:27.299 --> 00:08:28.592
Didn't I tell you?

82
00:08:49.528 --> 00:08:52.114
Stop it! I got C-4 in the trunk!

83
00:09:19.014 --> 00:09:21.641
Clive. guess what. man.

84
00:09:21.683 --> 00:09:24.602
I forgot to tell you.
I'm LAPD.

85
00:09:24.644 --> 00:09:26.020
You under arrest.

86
00:09:30.858 --> 00:09:33.860
Soo Yung. come on.
we're gonna be late.

87
00:09:33.860 --> 00:09:35.695
Let's go.

88
00:09:35.695 --> 00:09:37.572
Excuse me.

89
00:09:38.573 --> 00:09:39.699
What?

90
00:09:39.741 --> 00:09:41.701
Telephone. China.

91
00:09:44.620 --> 00:09:48.290
Soo Yung. I love you.
Have a nice day.

92
00:09:48.332 --> 00:09:50.084
Will you be home after school?

93
00:09:51.668 --> 00:09:55.047
I am going to pick you up
myself.

94
00:10:24.824 --> 00:10:27.326
When you walk by every night...

95
00:10:27.368 --> 00:10:29.495
talkin' sweet
and lookin' fine...

96
00:10:29.536 --> 00:10:33.498
I become hectic inside.

97
00:10:33.540 --> 00:10:36.501
Baby. I'm so into you.

98
00:10:36.543 --> 00:10:39.045
Darlin'. if you only knew...

99
00:10:39.087 --> 00:10:42.215
all the things
that float through my mind.

100
00:11:03.985 --> 00:11:05.236
Is there a problem. officer?

101
00:11:05.278 --> 00:11:07.613
No problem.

102
00:11:07.613 --> 00:11:09.114
Just rush hour.

103
00:12:04.165 --> 00:12:06.292
Security's in place?

104
00:12:06.334 --> 00:12:09.378
You're sure all of the exhibits
will be ready by this weekend?

105
00:12:09.420 --> 00:12:12.673
Yes. sir. Your opening remarks
are scheduled for 7:30.

106
00:12:12.714 --> 00:12:15.342
Excuse me. Consul Han.

107
00:12:15.384 --> 00:12:18.970
I'm Warren Russ with the
Federal Bureau of Investigation.

108
00:12:19.012 --> 00:12:21.014
This is Agent Whitney.

109
00:12:21.055 --> 00:12:22.807
We need to speak with you
in private.

110
00:12:25.393 --> 00:12:26.560
Excuse me.

111
00:12:34.234 --> 00:12:36.778
I know this is a difficult time
for you. Consul...

112
00:12:36.820 --> 00:12:39.197
but be assured
we'll get your daughter back.

113
00:12:39.239 --> 00:12:40.907
But will you get her back alive?

114
00:12:40.949 --> 00:12:44.410
We have the best agents
in the world on those streets.

115
00:12:45.536 --> 00:12:48.539
I would like
one of my people to help.

116
00:12:48.581 --> 00:12:52.543
Let me assure you. the FBI
considers this a top priority.

117
00:12:52.584 --> 00:12:54.878
We have plenty of people
on the case.

118
00:12:54.920 --> 00:12:57.756
Mr. Russ. I am not an American.

119
00:12:57.797 --> 00:12:59.841
My daughter is not an American.

120
00:12:59.883 --> 00:13:01.175
I understand that. sir--

121
00:13:01.217 --> 00:13:03.553
He's already on the plane.

122
00:13:03.594 --> 00:13:06.055
I trust you will treat him
with the same courtesy...

123
00:13:06.055 --> 00:13:08.057
as you have shown me.

124
00:13:12.227 --> 00:13:13.687
Ten people
jumped out of the trunk.

125
00:13:13.729 --> 00:13:16.565
I started handling all of them.
Throwing them everywhere.

126
00:13:16.606 --> 00:13:18.566
Then two stupid cops
came out of nowhere...

127
00:13:18.608 --> 00:13:20.568
messed everything up.
but then I regrouped.

128
00:13:20.610 --> 00:13:22.070
I had to save their life.

129
00:13:22.111 --> 00:13:24.238
It ain't in there.
Anyway. I save their life.

130
00:13:24.280 --> 00:13:26.282
I start runnin'.
trying to get the bomb--

131
00:13:26.324 --> 00:13:29.034
I can't believe
you went without me.

132
00:13:29.076 --> 00:13:30.744
I'll talk to y'all later.
all right?

133
00:13:30.786 --> 00:13:32.871
I'll tell you the best part
after work.

134
00:13:32.913 --> 00:13:34.873
This is why nobody
will work with you...

135
00:13:34.915 --> 00:13:38.168
why you're the only cop in the
department without a partner.

136
00:13:38.209 --> 00:13:41.296
Johnson. look. first of all.
if you want a date with me...

137
00:13:41.337 --> 00:13:43.923
you have to wait on the list
like every other woman. OK?

138
00:13:43.965 --> 00:13:46.050
Second of all. I work alone.

139
00:13:46.092 --> 00:13:49.136
I don't need no partner
and ain't never gonna have one.

140
00:13:49.178 --> 00:13:51.555
-Did Kojak have a partner?
-Yeah. The fat guy.

141
00:13:51.597 --> 00:13:53.724
He wasn't never with him.
Did Columbo?

142
00:13:53.765 --> 00:13:55.767
Captain Diel ordered me
to go with you...

143
00:13:55.767 --> 00:13:58.561
because you needed bomb squad
backup. but once again...

144
00:13:58.603 --> 00:14:00.105
you screwed me and yourself.

145
00:14:00.146 --> 00:14:01.814
Look. Johnson.
it's dangerous out there.

146
00:14:01.856 --> 00:14:04.192
It's safer for you
to be behind the desk.

147
00:14:04.233 --> 00:14:06.777
We were supposed to be
on the same team.

148
00:14:06.819 --> 00:14:09.154
Team?
Johnson. this is the LAPD...

149
00:14:09.196 --> 00:14:11.323
the most hated cops
in the free world.

150
00:14:11.365 --> 00:14:13.033
My own mama ashamed of me.

151
00:14:13.075 --> 00:14:14.910
She tell everybody
I'm a drug dealer.

152
00:14:14.951 --> 00:14:16.703
This is a pit stop for me.

153
00:14:16.745 --> 00:14:18.538
I'm on the verge of leaving
you suckers behind.

154
00:14:18.580 --> 00:14:21.249
Actually. you're on the verge
of being suspended.

155
00:14:21.291 --> 00:14:22.500
Have a nice day.

156
00:14:28.881 --> 00:14:30.591
Somebody told you
I was being suspended?

157
00:14:32.259 --> 00:14:34.052
Quit playin'. girl.

158
00:14:35.679 --> 00:14:37.514
I know you playin'.

159
00:14:38.807 --> 00:14:40.767
Somebody told you
I was being suspended?

160
00:14:43.436 --> 00:14:45.646
This is a problem.
That's all I need...

161
00:14:45.688 --> 00:14:47.440
some foreigner
getting his head blown off...

162
00:14:47.481 --> 00:14:49.108
and creating
an international incident.

163
00:14:49.149 --> 00:14:51.402
What can we do?
He's on his way.

164
00:14:53.320 --> 00:14:55.572
Call the field office.
Have them send over a rookie.

165
00:14:55.614 --> 00:14:58.116
We'll have him escort this guy
around a few days...

166
00:14:58.158 --> 00:15:00.577
pretend to follow some leads.
show him some sights...

167
00:15:00.618 --> 00:15:01.995
keep him out of our way.

168
00:15:02.036 --> 00:15:04.330
You want to do that
to one of men?

169
00:15:04.330 --> 00:15:06.123
What do you suggest?

170
00:15:07.833 --> 00:15:11.295
Well. as long as we're
gonna humiliate someone...

171
00:15:11.336 --> 00:15:13.338
might as well be LAPD.

172
00:15:15.799 --> 00:15:17.217
Even if I had an extra man...

173
00:15:17.259 --> 00:15:19.886
who would want
such a bullshit assignment?

174
00:15:19.928 --> 00:15:21.679
Well. it's a disgrace to me.

175
00:15:21.721 --> 00:15:23.681
It's a disgrace
to my department.

176
00:15:23.681 --> 00:15:24.974
It's a disgrace to--

177
00:15:26.851 --> 00:15:30.187
Dan. I'm sending someone
right over.

178
00:15:33.190 --> 00:15:36.485
Captain. I know you read
the paper. but they lying.

179
00:15:36.526 --> 00:15:37.944
I wouldn't do nothing like that.

180
00:15:37.986 --> 00:15:40.780
You know how the paper is.
They just want a story.

181
00:15:40.822 --> 00:15:43.658
Two officers were shot.
One man lost a pinkie.

182
00:15:43.699 --> 00:15:44.992
But didn't nobody die.

183
00:15:45.034 --> 00:15:47.828
-You destroyed half a block.
-That block was messed up.

184
00:15:47.870 --> 00:15:50.331
-You lost lots of evidence.
-We got a little left.

185
00:15:50.372 --> 00:15:53.417
What you did was dangerous
and completely against policy.

186
00:15:53.458 --> 00:15:56.253
And not only that...

187
00:15:56.294 --> 00:15:58.004
you did a good job.

188
00:15:59.089 --> 00:16:00.298
What?

189
00:16:00.340 --> 00:16:02.508
Everyone around here
is so image-conscious.

190
00:16:02.550 --> 00:16:05.052
Everybody's so afraid
of their own goddamn shadow.

191
00:16:05.094 --> 00:16:07.304
It's nice to meet
an L.A. detective...

192
00:16:07.346 --> 00:16:09.848
who's willing to lay it
on the line.

193
00:16:09.890 --> 00:16:13.310
Captain.
that's the same way I feel.

194
00:16:13.352 --> 00:16:15.228
That's what I've been trying
to tell everybody.

195
00:16:15.270 --> 00:16:18.189
Every so often. we have to let
the general public know...

196
00:16:18.231 --> 00:16:20.024
that we can still blow shit up.

197
00:16:20.066 --> 00:16:23.069
You goddamn right.
That's the only way I work.

198
00:16:23.111 --> 00:16:24.695
So that mean
I ain't gettin' suspended?

199
00:16:24.737 --> 00:16:27.239
-Are you kidding?
-Don't know why I said that.

200
00:16:27.281 --> 00:16:29.241
I just got a call from the FBI.

201
00:16:29.241 --> 00:16:31.368
The 10-year-old daughter
of a Chinese diplomat...

202
00:16:31.410 --> 00:16:34.538
was kidnapped this morning.
and they want you on the case.

203
00:16:34.579 --> 00:16:35.872
FBI want me?

204
00:16:35.914 --> 00:16:37.332
That's right.

205
00:16:37.374 --> 00:16:39.501
-Stop lying.
-I don't lie.

206
00:16:39.542 --> 00:16:41.211
-Tell the truth.
-I'm telling the truth.

207
00:16:42.420 --> 00:16:44.338
Thank you. Captain.

208
00:16:44.380 --> 00:16:47.550
Congratulations. Carter.
You are going to the show.

209
00:16:47.591 --> 00:16:50.135
I'll look out for you
when I reach the top.

210
00:16:50.177 --> 00:16:52.846
-I'm gonna make you mayor.
-I'd rather you didn't.

211
00:16:55.140 --> 00:16:58.601
Hey. listen up!
lf anybody need me...

212
00:16:58.601 --> 00:17:02.522
I'm gonna be workin'
a big. big case for the FBI!

213
00:17:19.245 --> 00:17:21.164
Yo. Take care of that for me.

214
00:17:35.010 --> 00:17:39.055
I need one of those earpieces
immediately. all right?

215
00:17:39.097 --> 00:17:40.473
Hey. how you doing?

216
00:17:40.515 --> 00:17:43.351
I want the consul's personnel
records cross-checked...

217
00:17:43.393 --> 00:17:45.853
with that new list
we received from Interpol.

218
00:17:45.895 --> 00:17:48.689
See if you can make
any matches or connections.

219
00:17:48.731 --> 00:17:50.649
OK. boys. what have we got?

220
00:17:50.691 --> 00:17:52.651
Have we checked the consul
personnel records yet?

221
00:17:52.693 --> 00:17:55.153
I want to know
who's he been talking with.

222
00:17:55.153 --> 00:17:56.780
OK. come on. Give me the story.

223
00:17:56.821 --> 00:17:59.449
Any demands? Any fingerprints?
Have we interviewed his staff?

224
00:17:59.491 --> 00:18:02.118
Whitney. who is this?

225
00:18:03.244 --> 00:18:04.954
Give me a copy of that.

226
00:18:04.996 --> 00:18:06.956
James Carter. FBI.

227
00:18:06.997 --> 00:18:09.833
Warren. he's here
for the special assignment.

228
00:18:12.127 --> 00:18:14.629
I'm Agent-In-Charge Warren Russ.

229
00:18:14.671 --> 00:18:17.173
It's good to have you onboard.

230
00:18:17.215 --> 00:18:18.633
I waited a long time for this.

231
00:18:18.675 --> 00:18:21.511
You guys sure take a long time
to process an application.

232
00:18:21.511 --> 00:18:25.139
Well. Carter.
your particular assignment...

233
00:18:25.181 --> 00:18:27.641
is considered G-14 classified.

234
00:18:27.683 --> 00:18:33.105
Why don't you and I take a walk
and I'll fill you in?

235
00:18:33.146 --> 00:18:34.398
OK. Warren.

236
00:18:39.861 --> 00:18:41.988
G-14 classified.

237
00:18:42.030 --> 00:18:43.656
That's good.

238
00:18:43.698 --> 00:18:45.825
You don't understand.
This is my dream.

239
00:18:45.866 --> 00:18:47.827
I'm very excited
about working with the FBI.

240
00:18:47.868 --> 00:18:50.829
I'm glad.
Listen. his name is Lee.

241
00:18:50.871 --> 00:18:53.498
And the director considers
this a top priority.

242
00:18:53.540 --> 00:18:56.334
No disrespect. but he's only
gonna get in my way.

243
00:18:56.376 --> 00:18:57.836
I'm not used
to having a partner.

244
00:18:57.877 --> 00:19:00.797
If I'm handling the situation.
I'm gonna have to work alone.

245
00:19:00.839 --> 00:19:03.091
Carter. he is the situation.

246
00:19:04.133 --> 00:19:05.760
Must be a misunderstanding.

247
00:19:05.801 --> 00:19:08.971
I was sent down here for
the kidnapping. Little girl?

248
00:19:09.013 --> 00:19:11.473
Forget the little girl.
Your assignment is Lee.

249
00:19:12.975 --> 00:19:14.768
Who and what kind of assignment
is that?

250
00:19:14.810 --> 00:19:18.271
Lee is a foreign detective
and a friend of the consul's.

251
